Yesterday, a listening session was hosted by Second Gentleman Douglas Emhoff, White House Domestic Policy Advisor Ambassador Susan Rice, Deputy Homeland Security Advisor Joshua Geltzer, U.S. Ambassador at Large for International Religious Freedom Rashad Hussain, and Office of Public Engagement Director Stephen Benjamin. The session was held with Muslim community leaders to discuss ways to counter Islamophobia, which refers to hate, discrimination, or bias towards individuals perceived to be Muslim. The Muslim leaders highlighted the challenges faced by their communities and provided recommendations to address Islamophobia and other forms of hate and bigotry. Biden-Harris administration officials expressed their appreciation for the leaders' efforts and emphasized President Biden's commitment to combating Islamophobia. This listening session is part of the ongoing efforts of the President's interagency task force to counter antisemitism, Islamophobia, and other forms of bias and discrimination in the United States.